00:10:11.830 --> 00:10:13.380
Best wishes, John Green.

00:10:13.380 --> 00:10:17.520
So continued defeat and the death of his troops
eventually convinced Napoleon to give up his

00:10:17.530 --> 00:10:22.620
dreams of an American empire and cut his losses.
He recalled his surviving troops, of the 40,000

00:10:22.620 --> 00:10:27.900
who left, only 8,000 made it back. And then,
he sold Thomas Jefferson Louisiana. And that

00:10:27.900 --> 00:10:32.400
is how former slaves in Haiti gave America
all of this.

00:10:32.400 --> 00:10:38.160
On January 1, 1804, Dessalines who had defeated
the French, declared the island of Saint-Domingue

00:10:38.160 --> 00:10:41.540
independent and re-named it Haiti, which is
what the island had been called by the native

00:10:41.540 --> 00:10:45.170
inhabitants before the arrival of Columbus.
The Haitian Declaration of Independence was

00:10:45.170 --> 00:10:49.950
a rejection of France and, to a certain degree
of European racism and colonialism.

00:10:49.950 --> 00:10:54.260
It also affirmed, to quote from the book Slave
Revolution in the Caribbean, “a broad definition

00:10:54.260 --> 00:10:59.320
of the new country as a refuge for enslaved
peoples of all kinds.” So, why is this little

00:10:59.320 --> 00:11:03.380
island so important that we would devote an
entire episode to it? First, Haiti was the

00:11:03.380 --> 00:11:07.150
second free and independent nation state in
the Americas. It also had one of the most

00:11:07.150 --> 00:11:11.240
successful slave revolts ever. Haiti became
the first modern nation to be governed by

00:11:11.240 --> 00:11:16.540
people of African descent, and they also foiled
Napoleon’s attempts to build a big new world empire

00:11:16.540 --> 00:11:20.490
Of course, Haiti’s history since its revolution
has been marred by tragedy, a legacy of the

00:11:20.490 --> 00:11:25.990
loss of life that accompanied the revolution.
I mean, 150,000 people died in 1802 and 1803

00:11:25.990 --> 00:11:30.440
alone. But the Haitian revolutions matter.
They matter because the Haitians, more than

00:11:30.440 --> 00:11:35.460
any other people in the age of revolutions,
stood up for the idea that none should be

00:11:35.460 --> 00:11:39.310
slaves, that the people who most need the
protection of a government should be afforded

00:11:39.310 --> 00:11:43.620
that protection. Haiti stood up for the weak
when the rest of the world failed to.

00:11:43.620 --> 00:11:47.340
The next time you read about Haiti’s
poverty, remember that.

